There is a 7-day Class BDR (deluxe restaurant) (on-sale) beer, wine and liquor license. This license may only be issued for the use of restaurants that:
Meet the definition requirements of "restaurant" established under the regulations of the Board of License Commissioners;
Have a minimum seating capacity of 150 persons for dining;
Have a cocktail lounge or bar area seating capacity not exceeding 25 percent of the seating capacity for dining;
Have parking facilities to accommodate a minimum of 75 vehicles; and
Have a minimum capital investment of $800,000 by the applicant exclusive of the cost of the land and buildings.
